I agree with Ben H and others about the sandwiches here.  The stuffed eggplant sandwich especially -- eggplant parm is just okay -- makes me a weekly customer at Calabria, which has impressed me since its days on Roosevelt in the spot currently occupied by Lola Coffee.  I used to go on Tuesdays for the $5 sandwich deal, but even when that promotion ended, I still pick up that yummy stuffed eggplant.  The location at 7th St. and Virginia seems prime for commuters, but the parking situation (two or three angled spots in front, more in back) seems to be a challenge.  I often find the place empty on weekday afternoons.  Going into summer, Calabria needs steady traffic, I imagine, to stay afloat.  I'm not sure if the recent Groupon promotion helped -- I hope so.

